reviews.review: No sure what they were going for.  It was a two hour Sci-Fi flick that is very watchable but not something I would pay money to watch again.
best Star Wars out of the 3 new ones

Critics who pan this movie are taking themselves far too seriously.  If you want to see a fun space fantasy, in which a group of flawed misfits band together to oppose an evil empire against overwhelming odds...and if you don't mind a few unanswered questions or open plot lines or escapes that defy the laws of physics...then grab a bucket of popcorn and your favorite soda (or beer), sit back, and enjoy the ride.  You're in for a treat.  You'll laugh a little, cry a little, and cheer a lot.  Enjoy!!
It was a great action-packed ending to a beloved series

Fantastic, action packed and full of emotional moments for long time fans of this historic tale.  Couldn't have asked for JJ to have done a better job completing the sequal trilogy having to pick up the pieces left in the wake of TLJ.  The only SW film that I've walked away from opening with a strong feeling of disappointment.  Please dont let the hollow reviews of some critics persuade you from seeing this film.  After all, those same critics gave high scores to the trainwreck known as The Last Jedi.

JJ Abrams did it. I wanted to close the book on my Star Wars fandom after my viewing of TLJ. But Abrams resurrected me. . I had hoped that he might, and boy did he ever. Empire will never be unseated as my number one, but Rise is a very close 2nd. Go see it all of you TLJ haters. You will be glad you did.

Overall, the movie was fantastic. But as a hardcore Reylo shipper, I am extremely upset by the end of the movie. It's one of those "I can't believe it happened and I loathe it, but I can't stop watching that scene on replay, thus torturing myself for probably years to come." It also doesn't feel 'done' for me, as if they left a little sense of an upcoming movie with Rey.
This was an extremely disappointing ending. It was basically a giant commercial. Then killing off a main character!? It was confusing and a hot mess. Waste of time and money.
